WEBVTT

00:02.536 --> 00:04.770
Well, what it boils down to is

00:04.772 --> 00:07.106
we've gotta take a closer look
at our bills.

00:07.708 --> 00:09.675
[grunts]

00:09.677 --> 00:12.311
Hey! What's going on in here?

00:12.313 --> 00:13.946
We're having a family meeting.

00:13.948 --> 00:17.549
Oh, I get it.
Freeze out the alien.

00:17.551 --> 00:19.818
I guess I'm not part
of the family.

00:19.820 --> 00:22.488
Uh, ALF, we thought you were
watching "The Three Stooges."

00:22.490 --> 00:24.490
I turned it off.

00:24.492 --> 00:28.460
Somehow I just can't buy
Shemp as a surgeon.

00:28.462 --> 00:30.829
- Curly was a senator once.
- True.

00:30.831 --> 00:33.732
And Moe was speaker
of the house.

00:33.734 --> 00:36.635
Could we, uh, put an end to the
stooge talk here for a minute?

00:36.637 --> 00:38.003
[imitating Curly]
Certainly.

00:38.005 --> 00:40.039
[gibberish]

00:42.343 --> 00:43.976
We'd like to get back
to our meeting.

00:43.978 --> 00:47.479
Oh, yeah.
The meeting I wasn't invited to.

00:47.481 --> 00:49.481
It's, uh, it's about
our family budget.

00:49.483 --> 00:50.983
What'd you think
I was going to do?

00:50.985 --> 00:53.352
Dominate the conversation?
Be a nuisance?

00:53.354 --> 00:54.686
No, ALF, nobody ever suggest--

00:54.688 --> 00:56.989
Throw up a lot of
pointless suggestions?

00:56.991 --> 00:58.757
- Interrupt everybody?
- Ah, we never said--

00:58.759 --> 01:00.426
Never let anyone get a word
in edgewise--

01:00.428 --> 01:04.530
ALF!
You can come to the meeting.

01:04.532 --> 01:06.131
No, thanks.

01:07.601 --> 01:09.835
[theme music]

01:20.414 --> 01:22.748
[no audio]

01:26.921 --> 01:29.188
[no audio]

01:33.894 --> 01:35.994
[no audio]

01:41.268 --> 01:43.635
[no audio]

02:01.989 --> 02:03.956
[no audio]

02:10.764 --> 02:12.064
Let's just take a look at
our electric bill for example

02:12.066 --> 02:13.932
it's three times
what it used to be.

02:13.934 --> 02:16.735
Maybe it's the porch light you
leave on every time I go out.

02:16.737 --> 02:18.904
Porch light stays.

02:18.906 --> 02:23.609
[chuckles]
And we've been keeping
the thermostat down to 70.

02:23.611 --> 02:26.578
And I turn off the dryer
as soon as I wake up.

02:26.580 --> 02:29.648
Well, we're just going..
The, the dryer?

02:29.650 --> 02:31.650
What do you mean
turn off the dryer?

02:31.652 --> 02:33.652
Why, why would you
even turn it on?

02:33.654 --> 02:35.921
To keep me company at night.

02:35.923 --> 02:38.824
Why? Is eight hours too long?

02:38.826 --> 02:39.925
Yes.

02:39.927 --> 02:42.628
What if I just leave it
on delicates?

02:42.630 --> 02:44.363
Leave it off.

02:44.365 --> 02:47.699
Now, let's get back to
the rest of our money problems.

02:47.701 --> 02:50.435
No chance of your getting
a better job I suppose.

02:50.437 --> 02:53.639
I like my job.
The money's fine.

02:53.641 --> 02:57.476
Who made this call to Munich?
Munich, Germany?

02:57.478 --> 03:00.145
Munich?
That has to be a mistake.

03:00.147 --> 03:02.181
No, it's not.

03:02.183 --> 03:04.650
You called Munich. Why?

03:04.652 --> 03:05.984
Remember the vacuum cleaner
I broke?

03:05.986 --> 03:07.386
Yeah.

03:07.388 --> 03:10.455
Well, the repair place said they
couldn't get the chicken salad

03:10.457 --> 03:12.224
out of the impeller blade

03:12.226 --> 03:14.793
and they had to send it
to Germany for an overhaul.

03:16.997 --> 03:19.364
That doesn't explain
why you'd call Germany.

03:19.366 --> 03:22.067
Hey, I believe in following
things through.

03:23.704 --> 03:26.038
Let's move on to
another problem.

03:26.040 --> 03:29.107
- Food.
- I'm gonna go get some cookies.

03:31.045 --> 03:35.214
I don't think that all of us
are aware how much food costs.

03:35.216 --> 03:39.117
We're all out of macaroons.
All we got are chocolate chips.

03:41.488 --> 03:46.291
Let alone how much food is being
consumed for that matter.

03:47.828 --> 03:49.094
Is something wrong?

03:50.531 --> 03:51.997
You're eating all our food.

03:52.566 --> 03:54.266
All the food?

03:57.004 --> 03:58.904
Except the stuff
that lands on the floor.

04:01.175 --> 04:05.377
Okay, I'm beginning to realize
what this is all about.

04:05.379 --> 04:07.546
You all think I'm a parasite.

04:07.548 --> 04:10.249
No one thinks you're a parasite.

04:10.251 --> 04:12.384
Alright. A freeloader?

04:12.386 --> 04:14.286
Freeloader is closer.

04:14.288 --> 04:15.954
What about a sponger?

04:15.956 --> 04:17.422
Where did you ever
hear that word?

04:17.424 --> 04:20.425
That's what<i> you</i> called him
last week.

04:20.427 --> 04:21.927
Oh, I see.

04:21.929 --> 04:25.230
Let's just settle on parasite
and move on.

04:25.232 --> 04:29.568
Fine. If you want me,
I'll be in my room.

04:29.570 --> 04:32.271
Not wasting money.

04:34.108 --> 04:36.141
[piano music]

04:44.918 --> 04:49.121
¶ I just checked into
the Parasite Hotel ¶

04:51.225 --> 04:54.860
¶ They ain't got a porter
or a bell ¶

04:56.263 --> 05:00.299
¶ I checked in
to that Parasite Hotel ¶¶

05:00.301 --> 05:02.668
- ALF!
- Oh, I'm sorry.

05:02.670 --> 05:04.336
Was I playing too loud?

05:04.338 --> 05:06.838
I didn't know
you could play the piano.

05:06.840 --> 05:08.340
Well, I was winging it.

05:08.342 --> 05:10.876
It's tough to play
without the red keys.

05:12.279 --> 05:13.945
You seem kinda down.

05:13.947 --> 05:18.350
Maybe I'm being overly sensitive
about being called a freeloader

05:18.352 --> 05:21.119
sponger and parasite.

05:21.121 --> 05:25.257
Oh, ALF, we didn't mean to call
you any of those things.

05:25.259 --> 05:28.660
You, you just happened
to catch us in a moment of..

05:28.662 --> 05:30.462
Honesty.

05:30.464 --> 05:33.265
It's just a matter of making
a few adjustments. You know we--

05:33.267 --> 05:37.636
No need to lay it out, Kateski.
I hear you loud and clear.

05:37.638 --> 05:39.805
I've gotta get a job.

05:39.807 --> 05:41.840
- A job?
- That's right.

05:41.842 --> 05:46.445
It's nose to the grindstone time
for this parasite.

05:46.447 --> 05:48.880
But, um, what could you even do?

05:48.882 --> 05:52.317
Well, on Melmac,
I owned and operated

05:52.319 --> 05:54.353
my own phlegm dealership.

05:55.556 --> 05:56.888
Phlegm dealership?

05:56.890 --> 06:00.892
Ever tried one?
The phlegm turbo was a classic.

06:02.062 --> 06:03.895
Must be some other options.

06:03.897 --> 06:05.230
Well, there was a sunroof

06:05.232 --> 06:08.834
but, uh, it was best
to keep it closed.

06:08.836 --> 06:12.137
Now, you don't need
to get a job.

06:12.139 --> 06:14.506
Listen, if you really wanna
contribute

06:14.508 --> 06:16.541
we'll give you a few chores
to do around the house.

06:16.543 --> 06:18.176
How would that be?

06:18.178 --> 06:21.079
You mean fluffing up pillows?
Stuff like that?

06:21.081 --> 06:24.182
Well, no, but you could, uh,
help fold laundry

06:24.184 --> 06:26.985
load the dishwasher.

06:26.987 --> 06:30.288
No. No, not that.
We'll think of something.

06:33.761 --> 06:35.494
Don't worry about it.

06:36.897 --> 06:39.831
Chores, fine for the beaver

06:39.833 --> 06:43.101
but not exactly
tycoon territory.

06:43.103 --> 06:47.038
Ah, I've gotta find a way
to earn money now.

06:47.040 --> 06:48.407
But how?

06:51.345 --> 06:55.414
"Looking for a way
to earn money now?

06:55.416 --> 06:58.517
Call this toll-free number."

06:58.519 --> 07:01.286
Opportunity knocks.

07:11.198 --> 07:14.866
Well, hello!
Yeah, uh, when do I start?

07:14.868 --> 07:17.769
Huh? Oh, oh, ALF.
My name is ALF.

07:17.771 --> 07:21.139
Yeah.
Have I earned any money yet?

07:21.141 --> 07:24.109
What do you mean
I have to sell something first?

07:24.111 --> 07:27.579
Alright, fine. Send it here
and I'll sell it.

07:27.581 --> 07:29.981
Uh, 167 Hemdale.

07:29.983 --> 07:32.717
It's a beige house.
You can't miss it.

07:32.719 --> 07:34.719
Yeah, great.
Oh, oh, wait a minute.

07:34.721 --> 07:37.489
Before I forget.
One more question.

07:37.491 --> 07:39.991
What am I gonna be selling?

07:39.993 --> 07:41.726
ALF, this package is for you.

07:41.728 --> 07:43.462
Oh, it's here. Yeah.

07:43.464 --> 07:44.763
What's here? What is it?

07:44.765 --> 07:45.897
Can I open it?

07:45.899 --> 07:47.666
Hey, hey, hey, come on.

07:47.668 --> 07:50.335
Let's not get impatient,
shall we?

07:53.073 --> 07:56.174
Tastefully packaged?
Well, I guess so.

07:57.611 --> 08:00.111
ALF, these are cosmetics.

08:00.113 --> 08:02.848
That's right, cosmetics.

08:02.850 --> 08:05.083
This must be
the earlobe freshener.

08:06.253 --> 08:08.253
ALF, what are you doing
with cosmetics?

08:08.255 --> 08:11.523
Huh? Oh, didn't I tell you?
I got a job.

08:11.525 --> 08:13.825
I'm a Terry Faith girl.

08:13.827 --> 08:15.026
I thought you were an alien.

08:15.028 --> 08:17.596
Why can't I have
the best of both worlds?

08:17.598 --> 08:20.031
But, ALF, how can you sell
Terry Faith cosmetics?

08:20.033 --> 08:23.268
Lynn, honey, I know exactly
what you're gonna say.

08:23.270 --> 08:25.337
I can't do
the public number, right?

08:25.339 --> 08:28.039
Ha! Well, just send
that worry packing.

08:28.041 --> 08:30.275
I make it all happen
over the phone.

08:30.277 --> 08:32.010
But don't you have to know
something about makeup

08:32.012 --> 08:33.445
before you can sell it?

08:33.447 --> 08:36.014
That's the great thing
about this company.

08:36.016 --> 08:39.384
They welcome ignorance.

08:40.821 --> 08:43.488
Have you ever had
a Terry Faith facial?

08:43.490 --> 08:44.990
Can't say that I have.

08:44.992 --> 08:46.958
You don't know anything
about this stuff.

08:46.960 --> 08:49.494
Honey, honey,
that's why we have this book.

08:49.496 --> 08:53.164
"The Wonderful World Of
Terry Faith Cosmetics."

08:53.166 --> 08:56.301
Let's check it out here.
Here we go.

08:56.303 --> 09:00.071
"Terry Faith was born
outside of Dayton, Ohio

09:00.073 --> 09:03.341
at a bend in the road
near the turn of the century."

09:03.343 --> 09:05.076
What does it says about
how to give a facial?

09:05.078 --> 09:06.912
Don't you wanna hear about
the early years?

09:06.914 --> 09:08.346
- I do.
- I don't.

09:08.348 --> 09:10.849
- Let's skip to the facial part.
- Alright, okay.

09:10.851 --> 09:12.083
Here we go.

09:12.085 --> 09:15.320
"Chapter I, the facial part."

09:15.322 --> 09:17.722
Here, hold this.

09:17.724 --> 09:18.990
Let's see here.

09:19.693 --> 09:21.826
This must be the stuff.

09:21.828 --> 09:25.564
Come on, Lynn, get down here.
Let's give it a shot.

09:25.566 --> 09:28.466
It says apply liberally
to customer's face and neck.

09:29.670 --> 09:32.070
What do you think?

09:32.072 --> 09:33.605
- Just a little bit.
- Yeah, yeah, okay.

09:34.708 --> 09:37.609
[humming]

09:37.611 --> 09:39.277
Yeah.

09:40.781 --> 09:42.847
Yeah, here it's going on
real smooth.

09:42.849 --> 09:45.216
- Just, just a little bit.
- It says apply liberally.

09:45.218 --> 09:47.218
Okay. Okay, apply liberally.

09:47.220 --> 09:48.219
Alright, that's what I'm doing.

09:48.221 --> 09:49.254
- Alright.
- Alright.

09:49.256 --> 09:50.855
Here we go. I'm applying it.

09:50.857 --> 09:51.957
- Okay
- Good. Okay. Good.

09:51.959 --> 09:54.893
Now, uh, now for cheek color

09:54.895 --> 09:58.396
I think Terry suggests
something like, uh

09:58.398 --> 09:59.731
Evening Lobster.

09:59.733 --> 10:01.566
- Can I see a mirror?
- Not yet, not yet.

10:01.568 --> 10:05.003
Now, I want you to suck in those
cheeks real tight. Like this.

10:06.640 --> 10:08.940
Superb. Let's do this.

10:08.942 --> 10:13.044
Here we go.
Oh, oh, yeah. Yeah.

10:13.046 --> 10:15.246
Here, uh, missed a spot
right there.

10:15.248 --> 10:18.283
- Great. Oh.
- Okay. Now can I see a mirror?

10:18.285 --> 10:20.085
I don't think you want to.

10:20.087 --> 10:21.920
My work speaks for itself.

10:21.922 --> 10:23.722
Come on. Let me have it.

10:26.660 --> 10:28.393
I'm gonna go wash my face.

10:28.395 --> 10:29.794
You didn't let it harden.

10:29.796 --> 10:31.363
Before it hardens.

10:32.766 --> 10:37.602
Brian, I'm in business.
My freeloader days are numbered.

10:37.604 --> 10:40.772
- What about your parasite days?
- Hey, come on now.

10:40.774 --> 10:43.775
Just help me pack this stuff up
and carry it to my room.

10:43.777 --> 10:45.710
[telephone ringing]

10:47.681 --> 10:51.282
Hello. Just a minute.

10:51.284 --> 10:54.085
ALF, it's for you.
Someone named Ginger.

10:54.087 --> 10:57.856
Oh, great. Great. Thanks.

10:57.858 --> 11:01.760
Hello, Ging. Darling!

11:01.762 --> 11:03.695
Oh, I just got the package.

11:03.697 --> 11:05.697
It's divine.

11:05.699 --> 11:07.499
Yeah, the lipsticks?

11:07.501 --> 11:10.669
I didn't know there were
so many luscious colors.

11:10.671 --> 11:15.940
Yeah. Oh, that tangerine tango
is exquisite.

11:15.942 --> 11:18.710
What? Couple of extra cases?

11:18.712 --> 11:21.312
Oh, yeah, no problem.
Mm-hmm, yeah.

11:21.314 --> 11:23.314
Yeah, send 'em over.
I'll move 'em.

11:23.316 --> 11:25.817
Yeah, just put it on my account.

11:25.819 --> 11:29.120
Yeah, okay. Thank you.<i> Ciao.</i>

11:29.122 --> 11:32.490
Alright, Brian,
I'm checking out.

11:32.492 --> 11:36.327
