11:46.173 --> 11:48.006
It's too quiet.

11:48.008 --> 11:50.208
- For reading?
- For the house.

11:50.210 --> 11:51.409
Where is ALF?

11:51.411 --> 11:53.178
Oh, I don't know.
He could be resting.

11:53.180 --> 11:54.546
He could be reading.

11:54.548 --> 11:56.381
He could be carrying our towels
through the den.

11:56.383 --> 11:57.882
- Excuse me, ALF.
- Yo.

11:57.884 --> 12:00.351
Why are you carrying our towels
through the den?

12:00.353 --> 12:03.154
Aren't we
a curious George tonight?

12:03.156 --> 12:05.824
[telephone ringing]

12:05.826 --> 12:07.092
Hello.

12:07.094 --> 12:08.727
We'd like an answer
to that question.

12:10.030 --> 12:12.197
It's for you.
Someone named Ginger.

12:12.199 --> 12:13.865
Oh, ho..
Here, hold this, hold this.

12:13.867 --> 12:15.233
Yeah.

12:16.570 --> 12:17.702
Hello.

12:17.704 --> 12:21.906
Hiya, Ging.
Yeah, what's cookin'?

12:21.908 --> 12:24.342
Uh-huh.
Yeah, uh-huh, oh..

12:24.344 --> 12:26.311
How's Oscar's hernia?

12:27.180 --> 12:28.847
Oh, good, that's good news.

12:30.517 --> 12:33.618
Oh, Ging, I couldn't agree more.

12:33.620 --> 12:39.591
Yeah, those hunting sashes
are going to be very hot.

12:39.593 --> 12:42.093
Yeah, yeah,
send me a ton of those.

12:42.095 --> 12:43.895
A hunting sashes?

12:43.897 --> 12:46.698
Newcomer of the month?<i> Moi?</i>

12:46.700 --> 12:49.367
Ha! Well, I don't know
what to say.

12:49.369 --> 12:52.036
I'm floored. I'm agog.

12:52.038 --> 12:54.539
I'm absolutely silly.

12:54.541 --> 12:56.474
(ALF)
'Yeah, okay, look,
gotta run, hun.'

12:56.476 --> 12:58.710
Love to Bridget and Peg.
Bye-bye.

12:58.712 --> 12:59.944
[kissing]

12:59.946 --> 13:02.580
- Yeah.
- Alright, alright.

13:02.582 --> 13:04.048
Let's just start
at the beginning.

13:04.050 --> 13:05.717
Who's Ginger?

13:05.719 --> 13:09.087
And why are you talking to her
about hunting sashes

13:09.089 --> 13:10.989
and if you'll pardon
my ignorance

13:10.991 --> 13:13.658
what are hunting sashes?

13:13.660 --> 13:16.294
Alright.
I was gonna tell you anyway.

13:16.930 --> 13:19.164
I have a job.

13:19.166 --> 13:20.999
- A what?
- A job.

13:21.001 --> 13:22.834
I'm in the rouge-slinging game.

13:23.603 --> 13:24.636
What?

13:24.638 --> 13:27.605
That's a trade lingo
for beauty rep.

13:27.607 --> 13:30.441
- What?
- I'm selling cosmetics.

13:30.443 --> 13:33.678
ALF, I thought we decided
against your getting a job.

13:33.680 --> 13:35.280
This isn't a job.

13:35.282 --> 13:38.516
It's a glittering,
fast pace career.

13:38.518 --> 13:41.252
If I play my cards right,
I can bring home twice

13:41.254 --> 13:44.022
what the civil servant
here does.

13:44.024 --> 13:46.791
The civil servant doesn't
need you to sell cosmetics.

13:46.793 --> 13:49.761
The civil servant is doing
just fine. Thank you very much.

13:51.364 --> 13:53.198
Mom, where are all the tow..

13:53.200 --> 13:55.800
Oh, the towels are in here.

13:55.802 --> 13:59.304
ALF, ALF was just about
to tell us why.

13:59.306 --> 14:03.174
Well, maybe he needed
some storage space.

14:03.176 --> 14:05.376
Oh, you can drop the cover,
Lynn.

14:05.378 --> 14:07.812
I've blown the lid off
of the Operation Makeup.

14:07.814 --> 14:10.648
Lynn, you mean you knew about
this and didn't tell us?

14:10.650 --> 14:13.051
Well, ALF asked me
not to say anything

14:13.053 --> 14:16.621
until he made enough money to
bail out the civil servant.

14:16.623 --> 14:19.891
Yeah, I mean, I finally
feel like a productive

14:19.893 --> 14:21.292
member of society.

14:21.294 --> 14:23.494
I'm pulling my weight, Willie.

14:23.496 --> 14:26.397
By selling cosmetics?

14:26.399 --> 14:29.234
Yeah, dad. He's really
excited about working.

14:29.236 --> 14:30.635
Let's give him a chance.

14:30.637 --> 14:32.837
Yeah, yeah. Wait till you
check out these goods.

14:32.839 --> 14:34.239
I'll be right back.

14:35.342 --> 14:36.975
You know, Willie.

14:36.977 --> 14:39.978
Honey, it's kind of nice
that he wants to help us out.

14:39.980 --> 14:44.916
Well, I guess we should be
supportive...for a while.

14:44.918 --> 14:46.918
And then, if he does manage
to show a profit

14:46.920 --> 14:47.986
not that we need it.

14:47.988 --> 14:49.821
Alright, here we go.

14:49.823 --> 14:51.222
Sit down, Katydid.

14:51.224 --> 14:54.392
Let's try to reverse
the ravages of time.

14:54.928 --> 14:56.227
What?

14:56.229 --> 14:57.528
Hey, come on,
don't fight it, Kate.

14:57.530 --> 14:59.497
It happens to everyone, alright?

14:59.499 --> 15:02.367
Willie, do I look old?

15:02.369 --> 15:06.104
Why are you
even listening to him?

15:06.106 --> 15:07.505
He is a beauty consultant.

15:08.675 --> 15:10.275
- Kate, honey.
- 'Mm-hmm.'

15:10.277 --> 15:11.843
- Listen to me, alright?
- 'Yeah.'

15:11.845 --> 15:13.044
And I mean this.

15:13.046 --> 15:15.847
It's not that you look old

15:15.849 --> 15:19.951
it's, it's just that a woman
of such radiant beauty

15:19.953 --> 15:25.189
should let her, her
lasting loveliness bloom

15:25.191 --> 15:26.791
with the passage of time.

15:27.861 --> 15:30.595
- Oh, brother.
- No, let him talk.

15:30.597 --> 15:32.730
We're all gonna be supportive,
remember?

15:32.732 --> 15:35.233
Alright, uh, ALF, maybe,
maybe I'll buy something.

15:35.235 --> 15:37.101
Um, what do you recommend?

15:37.103 --> 15:39.904
Well, uh, I say that, uh..

15:39.906 --> 15:42.807
...our sub-reflective
chin buffing paste is a must.

15:42.809 --> 15:46.644
- Really? How much is that?
- Fifty dollars.

15:46.646 --> 15:48.446
Or twenty.

15:48.448 --> 15:49.814
How much you got?

15:50.483 --> 15:52.917
- Five.
- Sold.

15:52.919 --> 15:56.487
You got a real flair for the
business end of the thing too.

15:56.489 --> 15:59.424
Hey, I didn't get voted Newcomer
Of The Month for nothing.

15:59.426 --> 16:03.328
[scoffs]
How could you be voted
Newcomer Of The Month

16:03.330 --> 16:05.430
when you haven't sold
anything yet?

16:05.432 --> 16:09.934
Ha! It's not how much you sell,
it's how much you buy.

16:09.936 --> 16:12.270
[doorbell rings]

16:12.272 --> 16:15.606
Well...exactly how much
did you buy?

16:15.608 --> 16:17.008
I'll have to check
my day planner.

16:18.278 --> 16:20.678
[doorbell rings]

16:25.452 --> 16:27.085
- William Tanner?
- Yes.

16:27.087 --> 16:29.620
I've got a delivery here for you
from the Terry Faith company.

16:29.622 --> 16:32.790
Hold it! Wait. Just a minute.
I'm not signing anything.

16:32.792 --> 16:37.028
No signature's necessary. This
was all paid for over the phone.

16:37.030 --> 16:39.597
I'll be back with the rest
when I get a bigger truck.

16:39.599 --> 16:41.599
Keep the faith.

16:43.470 --> 16:45.470
Four thousand dollars.

16:45.472 --> 16:48.673
Yup, that matches my total.

16:48.675 --> 16:52.477
ALF, how were you able to
purchase $4000 worth of makeup?

16:52.479 --> 16:55.346
Plastic. I put it on your visa.

16:55.348 --> 16:57.382
Oh, incidentally,
you're over your limit.

16:58.852 --> 17:03.521
You used my credit card
to buy $4000 worth of makeup?

17:03.523 --> 17:05.523
Hey, what choice did I have?

17:05.525 --> 17:08.526
Banks don't give a line of
credit to people with one name.

17:08.528 --> 17:10.495
Except Madonna.

17:10.497 --> 17:12.063
I don't believe this.

17:12.065 --> 17:13.865
Come on, you'll get it all back.

17:13.867 --> 17:16.634
The markup on this stuff
is outrageous.

17:16.636 --> 17:18.970
Here, look, you're already
five bucks ahead.

17:18.972 --> 17:24.342
ALF! ALF, ALF, what do you do
when the stuff turns green?

17:24.344 --> 17:25.643
Well, let's see here.

17:26.913 --> 17:31.049
Dayton, Dayton..
Her first marriage, puffy eyes.

17:31.051 --> 17:33.351
"Return to Dayton."
Oh, here we go.

17:33.353 --> 17:35.086
"When things turn green."

17:36.523 --> 17:38.856
What, you're gonna leave
the kid looking like that?

17:38.858 --> 17:41.259
Lynn, go help your brother
take his makeup off.

17:41.261 --> 17:42.627
Okay. Come on.

17:43.096 --> 17:44.796
[sighs]

17:46.699 --> 17:51.069
You have abused the trust
of this family far too long.

17:52.872 --> 17:54.038
You're grounded!

17:54.040 --> 17:57.075
Oh! No phone, no television,
no nothing!

17:57.077 --> 17:59.243
Not until we get this
makeup mess straightened out.

17:59.245 --> 18:03.247
My career really threatens you,
doesn't it, Willie?

18:03.249 --> 18:05.083
Yes, financially.

18:05.085 --> 18:06.517
Life's funny.

18:06.519 --> 18:09.387
You try and help someone out
and boom

18:09.389 --> 18:11.689
they turn on you
like a wild animal!

18:12.258 --> 18:14.058
[doorbell rings]

18:14.060 --> 18:15.593
If that's a load
of your deliveryman--

18:15.595 --> 18:17.728
No, that's probably the girls.

18:17.730 --> 18:21.132
- The girls?
- I'm sorry. The women.

18:21.134 --> 18:23.234
- What women?
- The customers.

18:23.236 --> 18:26.237
The ones coming
to the Terry Faith party.

18:26.239 --> 18:27.939
That's what the towels were for.

18:27.941 --> 18:30.141
It is, it's women.

18:30.143 --> 18:33.311
You are not to entertain
customers in this house.

18:33.313 --> 18:36.280
Of course, I'm not.
You are.

18:36.282 --> 18:37.815
What do you mean we are?

18:37.817 --> 18:39.951
I was trying to explain it
to you.

18:39.953 --> 18:42.787
See, your role in
a Terry Faith's sales family

18:42.789 --> 18:46.257
is to play host and hostess
to my customers.

18:46.259 --> 18:49.093
I-i-if that means selling
your makeup, forget it!

18:49.095 --> 18:51.796
Willie, Willie,
these products sell themselves.

18:51.798 --> 18:53.798
[doorbell rings]
You don't have to do a thing.

18:54.767 --> 18:58.102
Except entertain
a houseful of strangers.

18:58.104 --> 19:00.138
Relax.
They'll be wearing name tags.

19:00.140 --> 19:01.572
[doorbell rings]

19:01.574 --> 19:05.176
Oh, and by the way,
don't take any personal checks.

19:06.679 --> 19:07.845
[knock on door]
Willie!

19:07.847 --> 19:09.614
Don't worry, don't worry.

19:09.616 --> 19:12.683
I'm gonna put an end to this
right now.

19:12.685 --> 19:14.318
- Ladies--
- Oh, hi.

19:14.320 --> 19:17.688
- Oh, what a beautiful house.
- Hi, hi. No, I'm not ALF.

19:17.690 --> 19:19.824
Oh, then you must be
his assistant, Willie.

19:19.826 --> 19:22.860
- Where's ALF?
- ALF is at a, uh--

19:22.862 --> 19:24.428
- The director's meeting.
- Ooh.

19:24.430 --> 19:27.465
Yes, right. Uh, ladies, if I may
have your attention, please.

19:27.467 --> 19:28.799
About these products--

19:28.801 --> 19:30.334
Willie, hun,
you don't have to sell us

19:30.336 --> 19:31.869
the products sell themselves.

19:31.871 --> 19:34.672
- I'll have an espresso.
- Oh, gee, that sounds good.

19:34.674 --> 19:36.107
Could you sprinkle a little
cinnamon on mine

19:36.109 --> 19:38.476
and don't bother
to heat the strudel.

19:38.478 --> 19:41.112
Espresso and strudel.

19:41.114 --> 19:42.880
Uh, listen, ladies,
I don't know what ALF told you

19:42.882 --> 19:44.315
about these cosmetics--

19:44.317 --> 19:45.983
Oh, never mind, here they are.

19:45.985 --> 19:48.819
Is it okay if we open these..
Stop.

19:48.821 --> 19:52.823
No, no.
That's not a good idea. No, no.

19:52.825 --> 19:55.059
- Oh, is that espresso coming?
- And strudel?

19:55.061 --> 19:56.460
Uh, I'll see.

19:56.462 --> 19:59.764
Oh, Willie, did the muffin-free
eye solvent finally come in?

20:01.534 --> 20:03.834
Kate.

20:03.836 --> 20:06.737
Tell the girls to hang on.
The food is on its way.

20:07.373 --> 20:10.374
Cinnamon.

20:10.376 --> 20:13.978
What am I doing? We don't even
have an espresso machine.

20:13.980 --> 20:17.148
Too bad. It's kinda standard
at these parties.

20:17.150 --> 20:19.250
Look, let them start on these.
I'll make some instant.

20:20.653 --> 20:22.887
You're not making anything.
The party is over.

20:22.889 --> 20:25.756
[doorbell rings]
Willie is not doing
his card tricks again, is he?

20:25.758 --> 20:27.558
Yeah, that's..

20:27.560 --> 20:29.527
- Hi.
- Oh, come in.

20:29.529 --> 20:32.530
Look, what...wait till you see.
They've got all the shades.

20:32.532 --> 20:33.898
- 'Wait..'
- Oh, that's wonderful.

20:33.900 --> 20:35.900
Oh, Willie,
I don't wanna ruin my manicure.

20:35.902 --> 20:38.869
Would you rub this in for me?

20:38.871 --> 20:43.107
- Oh...where?
- Wherever I need it.

20:50.583 --> 20:52.783
- Willie..
- Oh, hi, Kate.

20:52.785 --> 20:57.722
- Uh, can we change a $100 bill?
- A $100?

20:57.724 --> 20:59.090
Oh, Willie,
never mind the change.

20:59.092 --> 21:01.559
I'll take this
and the guacamole skin toner

21:01.561 --> 21:03.094
and we'll call it even.

21:03.096 --> 21:06.297
Guacamole skin toner.
I've gotta have some of that.

21:06.299 --> 21:08.266
Oh, did someone say guacamole?

21:08.268 --> 21:09.900
- Willie, what's going on?
- I don't know.

21:09.902 --> 21:11.902
But, uh,
I think we sold something.

21:11.904 --> 21:14.105
Willie, will you take
personal checks?

21:14.107 --> 21:16.307
Oh, I don't know.
Uh, should we?

21:16.309 --> 21:18.242
(ALF)
'Get some ID.'

21:18.244 --> 21:20.044
Get some ID.

21:20.046 --> 21:22.747
Willie, I think I bought enough
to qualify for the luggage.

21:22.749 --> 21:23.981
What luggage?

21:23.983 --> 21:25.216
Well, ALF told me
I get my choice

21:25.218 --> 21:27.318
of either soft sided
or mock Naugahyde

21:27.320 --> 21:29.720
and I'd like to see them
before I make my choice.

21:29.722 --> 21:31.656
I don't know
what you're talking about, lady.

21:31.658 --> 21:33.924
ALF said you'll try
to talk me out of it.

21:33.926 --> 21:36.227
Myrna, uh, forget the luggage.

21:36.229 --> 21:39.597
Just buy another $200 worth
and take the trip to Dayton.

21:39.599 --> 21:41.799
You'll love the museum.
It's marvelous.

21:41.801 --> 21:43.301
Great idea.

21:43.303 --> 21:46.103
Willie, honey, do you think
we're doing the right thing?

21:46.105 --> 21:47.905
I don't know.
We've got no choice.

21:47.907 --> 21:49.840
We're in this up to our necks.

21:49.842 --> 21:52.410
Necks?
Oh, that reminds me.

21:52.412 --> 21:55.446
Willie dear, where is that
neck tightener I ordered?

21:55.448 --> 21:57.281
Coming, bunny.

21:57.283 --> 21:58.849
I'll be right back, dear.

22:00.286 --> 22:01.852
Cheez Whiz?

22:03.990 --> 22:05.990
Hey, Tanner,
the rest of your stuff is here.

22:05.992 --> 22:08.359
Should I back the truck up to
the door or what?

22:09.295 --> 22:12.163
[instrumental music]

22:14.500 --> 22:16.200
[instrumental music]

22:19.138 --> 22:21.138
Well, all the figures are in.

22:21.140 --> 22:24.175
- How much did we make?
- Not so fast.

22:24.177 --> 22:25.710
I need a drumroll.

22:25.712 --> 22:26.977
Just tell us.

22:26.979 --> 22:29.246
I'm not telling you
until I get a drumroll.

22:30.149 --> 22:32.216
Give me that.

22:32.218 --> 22:33.451
Well..

22:33.453 --> 22:34.952
Now, we did pretty well.

22:34.954 --> 22:38.489
Pretty well? We made it all back
plus a small profit.

22:38.491 --> 22:41.292
Oh, boy, can we get
an air-hockey table?

22:41.294 --> 22:43.994
No, I think
we'll just use this money

22:43.996 --> 22:46.297
to pay for that phone call
to Munich.

22:46.299 --> 22:48.532
You know, if we have few more
of these parties--

22:48.534 --> 22:51.335
No, no more parties.
No more makeup.

22:51.337 --> 22:52.937
No more Terry Faith.

22:54.040 --> 22:56.474
Well, I want you all to know

22:56.476 --> 22:59.477
how much I appreciate
your giving me the chance.

22:59.479 --> 23:02.346
You came through for me,
and it all worked out

23:02.348 --> 23:06.016
and now,
I've got something for you.

23:06.018 --> 23:09.053
Lynn, tell them
what they've won.

23:09.055 --> 23:14.759
You have just won a beautiful
set of mock Naugahyde luggage.

23:16.162 --> 23:20.564
ALF, that is really,
really sweet.

23:20.566 --> 23:23.367
It looks just like
real Naugahyde.

23:23.369 --> 23:25.603
And that's only
the beginning, folks.

23:25.605 --> 23:29.340
Because next week,
we'll be packing those bags

23:29.342 --> 23:32.543
and leaving
for beautiful Dayton

23:32.545 --> 23:34.845
'where we'll be spending
three days and two nights'

23:34.847 --> 23:37.782
at the beautiful
Terryland Hotel.

23:37.784 --> 23:42.720
You'll be dancing and dining in
the beautiful eye shadow lounge

23:42.722 --> 23:45.956
and visiting
the Terry Faith museum

23:45.958 --> 23:49.193
where Terry herself
is on display

23:49.195 --> 23:52.463
gorgeously preserved in the
revolving crystal casket.

23:53.933 --> 23:56.133
"To preserve the dignity
of this monument

23:56.135 --> 23:58.302
there will be no
flash photography."

23:58.971 --> 24:02.139
[instrumental music]

24:03.876 --> 24:06.310
[theme music]

24:30.470 --> 24:32.303
<i> [ALF laughing]</i>
